description: A truck driver is on the run after an allegedly stolen eight-wheeled flatbed truck smashed into homes and cars in Campbelltown in the early hours of the morning.

title: TikTok star Haley Odlozil dies cancer aged 30 five years after diagnosed with the terminal illness
description: Haley Odlozil, 30, who began documenting her life on TikTok following her Stage IIIC ovarian cancer diagnosis in 2015, has passed away. The heartbreaking news was shared by husband, Taylor.

title: Charlie Teo to work in China as family of victim speaks out after guilty verdict about his conduct
description: Controversial neurosurgeon Charlie Teo has revealed he plans to perform brain surgery in China following this week's adverse findings against him as the family of one of his victims speaks out.

title: UK's richest divorcee Kirsty Bertarelli unveils new boyfriend two years after receiving £350million
description: Staffordshire-born former Miss UK Kirsty Bertarelli is singing for joy, as she hosted a joint birthday party with her new boyfriend in Sardinia.

title: ELIZABETH WINDER takes a look at the groupies who made The Rolling Stones
description: ELIZABETH WINDER: They were grubby adolescents still wearing clothes bought by their mums. Then they met a cadre of sophisticated women, and a magical alchemy was born.

title: EDEN CONFIDENTIAL: Jeremy Clarkson's friend quits as chairman of Prince Harry's charity
description: EDEN CONFIDENTIAL: Jack Hornby's departure from Sentebale has prompted Harry to pay tribute to his 'leadership and vision' and 'dedication, partnership and friendship'.

title: Neighbors of Gilgo Beach serial murder suspect 'feel like they're living in true crime documentary'
description: A seedy party atmosphere has sprung up outside the home of accused serial killer Rex Heuermann, with Mackenzie Richards even bringing her pet pig to the scene while beer-swigging gawkers filled the street.

title: Famous SOLO Man character from 1980s ad is preparing to make a return as CUB release new version
description: A new alcoholic version of the classic Australian soft drink Solo has renewed hopes of a return to screens of the legendary character from ads screened in the 1970s and '80s.

title: PLATELL'S PEOPLE: What's next for Huw? No - What's next for his poor wife and kids?
description: PLATELL'S PEOPLE: Vicky's statement, delivered just minutes after the Met police revealed no criminal act had been committed, was almost pitifully pleading.

title: Transgender runner, 49, wins women's 400m medal at the World Para Athletics Championships in Paris
description: Valentina Petrillo's place on the podium meant that Morocco's Fatima Ezzahra El-Idrissi missed out in a medal during the T12 final for visually impaired athletes.

title: Orange NSW house fire leaves James Richings and his two boys facing homelessness
description: A tragic house fire that killed a mother-of-two at Orange, NSW has left a father and his sons full of grief but also living week to week in temporary accommodation, fearing homelessness.

title: ANDREW NEIL: Britain's sick note culture is ruining us. But politicians have no answer
description: ANDREW NEIL: According to a report from the Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR) published this week, there are now 5.3 million Brits of working age claiming out-of-work benefits, a modern record.

title: SANTA MONTEFIORE reveals how six months after her death, her sister's spirit sat on her bed
description: SANTA MONTEFIORE never got the chance to say goodbye to her famous sibling Tara Palmer-Tomkinson. But here she reveals how her gift for seeing spirits led to an unexpected reunion.

title: By-election candidate uses AI to create manifesto
description: Andrew Gray, a lawyer who is standing as an independent, used a machine learning tool called Polis to aggregate the policy positions of thousands of voters in Selby and Ainsty.

title: Judy Murray joins battle to save one of Britain's oldest tennis clubs
description: The multimillionaire landlords want to bulldoze Badgers Tennis Club in Brighton to pave the way for luxury homes sparking Andy Murray's mother to get involved.

title: MARK PALMER: As airport workers vote for strikes the more things change the more they stay the same
description: MARK PALMER: The prospect of thousands of flights being affected across Europe when air traffic controllers walk out is not a pretty picture.

title: DR MICHAEL MOSLEY: Don't let your voice age you, practise singing in the shower!
description: DR MICHAEL MOSLEY: Although we are all too aware of the greying hair and expanding waistline as we age, those sometimes subtle changes that happen to our voices over time may be less obvious.

title: Stay away from playgrounds, men at Britain's first asylum camp in Essex ordered
description: Up to 1,700 men will be housed at the Essex base and another 2,000 at the Dambusters' former base, RAF Scampton in Lincolnshire after legal challenge by two councils.

title: Lindisfarne Hobart: why tenants of this timber-floored house will live rent-free when they move in
description: The three-bedroom home overlooks Mount Wellington for $525 per week and for the first two weeks, tenants can put the cost of rent towards the cost of moving instead.

title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: So how would pious peers stop the boats?
description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: The rift between those who genuinely want to stop illegal migration to this country and those who don't is now one of the defining features of British politics.

title: Panic as 'life saving' iPhone app for diabetics stops working on some devices
description: The FreeStyle Libre app works by monitoring blood sugar levels through a small sensor inserted into the body and provides real-time updates to a mobile phone.

title: Brother of Gilgo Beach serial murders suspect is KILLER who fatally struck police captain in 1988
description: The suspect arrested in connection with Long Island's Gilgo Beach murders has an older brother who killed a police captain in 1988 after striking him with his car while high on cocaine.

title: Could baby brain be a myth? Study finds that women with young children have just as good a memory
description: It's a widely held belief that new mothers suffer from 'baby brain' and are prone to forgetfulness and foggy thinking, but a study suggests this may be a myth.

title: Crown Prince of Saudi Arabia Mohammed bin Salman receives invitation to come to Britain
description: In a bid to deepen ties with the oil-rich Gulf state, the UK Government has invited Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman to visit this autumn.

title: Will you be the next victim of the car cannibals?
description: All these owners were only the latest victims of an alarming new crime trend, which involves cars being stripped and left in situ rather than stolen outright.

title: Now Just Stop Oil protesters interrupt live recording of Channel 4 show The Last Leg
description: Three eco-activists wearing Just Stop Oil t-shirts ran onto the set before handing Hills and his fellow comics Josh Widdicombe and Alex Brooker, their orange branded Hi Vis vests.

title: Minister orders investigation after tampons and sanitary pads found being supplied in MEN'S toilets
description: UK Environment Secretary Therese Coffey has called for a probe after it was revealed feminine hygiene products are regularly replenished in the men's loos, as well as the women's toilets at Defra.

title: Cops feared Gilgo Beach serial murder suspect would strike again
description: Cops had Heuermann under tight surveillance since last year, and had planned to continue to follow him as they built their case, but decided to swoop in on him in the interest of 'public safety.'

title: ROBERT HARDMAN: Labour's obsession with ULEZ could save the Conservatives in Uxbridge
description: ROBERT HARDMAN: As of next Thursday, the people of Uxbridge and West Ruislip may well be represented by the Invisible Man.

title: I know who killed the Princes in the tower, says DOMINIC SANDBROOK
description: DOMINIC SANDBROOK: The fate of the 12-year-old Edward V and his nine-year-old brother Richard, Duke of York, who vanished in the summer of 1483, has inspired armchair sleuths.
